From David Sternlight Subject Re Once tapped your code is no good any In article Arthur Rubin writes I wouldn't think Asking people to trust a secret algorithm seems unsound to Maybe so but it's quite There are millions of Macintosh users who have no idea what's in Apple's patented Many have modems How do you know all your business secrets aren't being stolen Answer Because you trust Apple Because if any such attempt however sophicsticated came out it would destroy Apple's credibility In the Clipper case a representative body of experts is going to be allowed to audit it and we'll have assurances maybe even from the President that other than the escrowed keys there are no back While some may not have confidence in that I am not among them it's a lot more assurance than we get for many things we routinely trust in everyday David David Sternlight Great care has been taken to ensure the accuracy of our information errors and omissions